The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for predicting customer lifetime value in video games, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the importance of identifying valuable players and maximizing their lifetime value, which relates to game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of big data and the need for efficient computational methods, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and cryptography (cs.CR).
